  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "AWS Network Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Overview</strong><br />We are seeking an experienced <strong>AWS Network Engineer</strong> to join our Digital Systems team. In this role, you will be responsible for designing, building, and maintaining robust network infrastructure both within AWS and across hybrid environments. You’ll ensure reliable connectivity, secure network operations, and efficient cloud networking practices to support mission‑critical services.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage and support Palo Alto Firewalls and GlobalProtect VPN.</li><li>Configure, monitor, and troubleshoot AWS networking (VPC, security groups, route tables, etc.).</li><li>Handle network incidents and service requests in line with ITIL processes.</li><li>Work closely with infrastructure, security, and cloud teams to ensure secure connectivity.</li><li>Maintain up-to-date network documentation, configurations, and change records.</li><li>Communicate clearly with internal teams and stakeholders.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Hands-on experience with cloud platforms (AWS preferred).</li><li>Knowledge of AWS networking services (VPC, NAT Gateway, Load Balancers).</li><li>Basic understanding of ITIL (Incident, Change, Problem Management).</li><li>Strong collaboration, documentation, and communication skills.</li><li>Cloud and/or networking certifications (AWS, Azure, GCP) are a plus.</li></ul><p><strong>Work Location: </strong>North<br /><br />(EA Reg No: 20C0312)<br />Please email a copy of your detailed resume to <strong>qianyu@talentsis.com.sg</strong> for immediate processing.<br />Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
